description: TEHRAN- The latest protests among college students in the US in support of the Palestine cause are a necessary part of the big puzzle of revealing the true face of American democracy and internal problems and political dependencies.
title: The pro-Palestinian protests show the real face of American “democracy”

description: The United Nations General Assembly has backed a Palestinian bid to become a full UN member by recognizing it as qualified to join and recommending the UN Security Council “reconsider the matter favorably”.
title: UN General Assembly backs Palestinian bid for membership

description: Three Israeli whistleblowers working at the Sde Teiman desert camp, a holding site for Palestinians detained during Israel’s invasion of Gaza, have claimed to have witnessed a series of abuses by the military, including prisoners being restrained, blindfolded, and forced to wear diapers, CNN reported.
title: CNN: Whistleblowers detail abuse of Palestinians in Israeli prison

description: About 110,000 people have fled Rafah in southern Gaza and food and fuel supplies in the area are critically low, a United Nations official said.
title: UN: About 110,000 people flee Rafah

description: Fighters from the Lebanese Hezbollah resistance movement have carried out a strike against Israeli military positions in the northern side of the occupied territories in response to brutal aggression against the Gaza Strip.
title: Hezbollah hits Israeli military positions

description: An independent non-profit body that tracks political violence and political protests around the world found that 97% of campus demonstrations over the war in Gaza that have taken place in the US since mid-April have been peaceful.
title: Study: Nearly all Gaza campus protests have been peaceful

description:
* Saleh Sharifi is putting his latest paintings on view in an exhibition at Bavan Gallery.
Entitled “Hidden Murmurs”, the exhibit will run until May 27 at the gallery located at 7 Abdo off Lareztan St. off Motahhari Ave.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN-The Persian translation of the novel “Journey by Moonlight” written by the Hungarian author Antal Szerb has been released in the bookstores across Iran.
title: Antal Szerb’s best-known work “Journey by Moonlight” hits bookstores

description: TEHRAN-The play “Art” written by the French writer Yasmina Reza will begin its performances at Iranshahr Theater in Tehran from mid-May.
title: Yasmina Reza’s “Art” to be performed at Iranshahr Theater

description: TEHRAN-Iranian composer and orchestra leader Mehdi Vojdani has recently unveiled an innovative arrangement of regional music.
title: Composer Mehdi Vojdani blends tradition, innovation in new regional music arrangement

description: TEHRAN-The pavilion of Yemen, the special guest of the 35th Tehran International Book Fair (TIBF) opened on Thursday at the Tehran’s Imam Khomeini Mosalla (prayer grounds).
title: Yemen’s presence at 35th TIBF as special guest deepens cultural relations between two nations

description: TEHRAN- A high-ranking commander within the Iranian Army has underscored the importance of directing the new generation’s attention toward content creation in the domain of Sacred Defense.
title: Iranian commander emphasizes educating youth on Sacred Defense principles

description: TEHRAN - In a note, Kayhan discussed the recent visit of President of Kurdistan Region Nechirvan Barzani and wrote: The Kurdistan authorities of Iraq concluded that by talking and getting closer to Tehran, they will reduce the threats of Tehran targeting them.
title: The Kurdistan Region of Iraq seeks to de-escalate tensions with Iran

description: TEHRAN- Former Iranian Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif has launched a critique of U.S. President Joe Biden's handling of the 2015 Iran nuclear یeal, labeling it as "reckless lawlessness" reminiscent of his predecessor's errors.
title: Ex FM: Is the world better off without Iran Nuclear Deal?

description: TEHRAN - Iran and the United Arab Emirates have resumed their joint consular commission meetings in Abu Dhabi after a decade-long pause.
title: Iran, UAE hold 10th joint consular commission meeting after decade-long pause

description: TEHRAN- Iranian Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian warned on Thursday that Israel’s plans to carry out a long-awaited all-out military offensive against Rafah, which is home to 1.5 million displaced Palestinians, would result in another human disaster in the region.
title: Israeli genocide in Rafah will spell another human disaster in region: FM

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian Army’s Commander-in-Chief, Major General Abdul Rahim Mousavi, has stated that operations "Al-Aqsa storm" and "True Promise" have hastened the downfall of the Zionist entity oppressing and harming children.
title: Operation "Al-Aqsa Storm" and "True Promise" hastened Israel's downfall

description: TEHRAN – Iranians show up in large numbers for a pivotal second-round runoff election to finalize the lineup of the country's parliament.
title: Iranians vote in parliamentary runoff as Leader calls for strong voter turnout

description: TEHRAN- A leaked report has thrown a spotlight on Britain’s active complicity in Israel’s genocidal war on Gaza.
title: Britain’s complicity in Gaza war

description: MADRID - In recent days, the BBC published alleged documents classified as "confidential" belonging to the Islamic Revolution Guards. According to the British media, these documents included the names of the alleged killers of the young Nika Shakarami, as well as the officers responsible for covering up the case.
title: Unpacking a BBC report

description: TEHRAN - Since the Israeli occupation regime launched its relentless bombardment against women and children in the Gaza Strip, the United States provided unequivocal support for Tel Aviv.
title: Behind U.S. warning of Israeli arms suspension

description: TEHRAN- Iran says that the current suppression of pro-Palestine student demonstrations in the West shows that the U.S. and Europe prioritize their backing for Israel over their commitments to uphold human rights.
title: Tehran asserts U.S., EU prioritize Israeli regime over human rights

description: TEHRAN – In the past five years, Western powers have repeatedly lost the chances to revive the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA), as they seem to believe that with or without a deal, Iran is unlikely to move towards making drastic changes to its nuclear doctrine.
title: Nuclear signal

description: TEHRAN - Persepolis will continue their quest to reclaim top spot in the Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL) when they face Havadar on Matchday 27.
title: Persepolis force a decider against Havadar

description: TEHRAN – Some historical earthenware has recently been unearthed in a serendipitous find when workers excavated the floor of a bank nestled within the bustling grand bazaar of Isfahan.
title: Historical earthenware unearthed in downtown Isfahan

description: TEHRAN – Assessments suggest that relics recently found in Hamedan date from the early Islamic era, particularly from the Ilkhanid epoch (1256-1335), a local official said on Friday.
title: Relics found in Hamedan date from Ilkhanid era, official says

description: TEHRAN – Believed to be among the hottest spots on Earth, UNESCO-listed Rig-e Yalan, situated within Iran’s Lut desert, is a diamond in the rough which could shine bright as a touristic destination, according to experts.
title: Desert tourism: hidden gem lies in South Khorasan

description: TEHRAN – On Thursday, the Iranian tourism minister arrived in Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari province, where he toured several key historical sites and participated in a regional tourism commission.
title: Minister inspects Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari attractions

description: TEHRAN – Fars’s tourism chief has announced plans to restore the UNESCO-registered Sassanid Archaeological Landscape, which is situated in the southern Iranian province.
title: UNESCO-listed Sassanian landscape to undergo restoration

description: TEHRAN –Each year the World Migratory Bird Day is celebrated on May 11 to raise awareness about the importance of migratory birds and the need to protect them.
title: ‘Protect insects, protect birds’

description: TEHRAN – Adolescents Well-being and Empowerment Centers, known as MASERRAT, in Mashhad and Kermanshah cities have revised and reviewed their protocols to make sure the adolescent girls receive the most efficient and high-quality services.
title: Services in adolescent empowerment centers to be enhanced

description: TEHRAN – The International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent (IFRC) has expressed willingness to expand collaboration with the Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS).
title: IFRC seeks to boost co-op with IRCS

description: TEHRAN – The heads of the chambers of commerce of Iran and Poland have explored ways of increasing the level of cooperation between the private sectors of the two countries in an online meeting.
title: Iran, Poland private sectors discuss bilateral cooperation

description: TEHRAN - The official data of the United States show that the country’s trade with the Islamic Republic of Iran has doubled and grew more than 100 percent in the first quarter of this year.
title: Iran-U.S. trade doubles in Q1 2024

description: TEHRAN - Managing director of the Iran Fuel Conservation Company (IFCO) Hosain Abniki, says energy consumption in Iran is more than double the world standards.
title: Energy consumption in Iran twice world standards, says official

description: TEHRAN -  Iran's Oil Minister Javad Oji says the country’s oil production has increased by 60 percent in the current government starting August 2021, Shana reported.
title: Iran's oil production up by 60% in 2.5 years: Oji

description: TEHRAN - The ambassadors of Uganda, Kenya, Senegal, and Burkina Faso in Tehran discussed the updates about their countries in the energy field, expressing their readiness to collaborate with Iran in a meeting dubbed "Perspective of Oil and Gas Industry in Africa".
title: African states welcome collaboration with Iran on oil, gas projects

description: TEHRAN - The Armenian government has announced that it is going to borrow $254 million from the European Bank of Reconstruction and Development (EBRD) to build a 24-kilometer section of a new highway leading to the Iranian border.
title: Armenia to build a new highway leading to Iran

description: TEHRAN - The UK Department of Trade and Industry said the country’s import of goods and services from Iran in 2023 exceeded £200 million, showing a 15.5 percent growth compared to a year earlier.
title: Iran exports £200m goods, services to UK in 2023

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s Minister of Transport and Urban Development Mehrdad Bazrpash said the meeting of the Iran-Turkey Joint Economic Committee will be held in Tehran in the coming weeks.
title: Tehran to host Iran-Turkey Joint Economic Commission soon

description: TEHRAN - The head of the National Iranian Gas Company (NIGC) said the gas contract between Iran and Iraq, which would finish on June 20, 2024, has been extended for another five years, Mehr News Agency reported.
title: Iran, Iraq extend gas deal for another 5 years

description:
Thousands of pro-Palestinian demonstrators marched in the Swedish port city of Malmo against Israel’s participation in the pan-continental Eurovision Song Contest.
Contest organisers, who say the event should be nonpolitical, resisted calls to exclude Israel over its war on Gaza.
title: Thousands march in Sweden’s Malmo against Israel’s Eurovision participation
